Do Not Track
Currently, various browsers ‚Äî such as Internet Explorer, Firefox, and Safari ‚Äî offer a ‚Äúdo not track‚Äù or ‚ÄúDNT‚Äù option that relies on a technology known as a DNT header, which sends a signal to Web sites‚Äô visited by the user about the user's browser DNT preference setting. Black Ace Media Inc does not currently commit to responding to browsers' DNT signals with respect to the Company's Web sites, in part, because no common industry standard for DNT has been adopted by industry groups, technology companies or regulators, including no consistent standard of interpreting user intent. Black Ace Media Inc takes privacy and meaningful choice seriously and will make efforts to continue to monitor developments around DNT browser technology and the implementation of a standard.
